<p> You could define what songs are indie rock based on what Spotify tells you,
    but personally I like to go on vibes. To me, indie rock is melodic/echo-y guitars,
    understated vocals, and metaphoric lyrics. In today’s music, rock is often combined
    with other genres and sounds such as pop, folk, and electronic. Because of this,
    it can be difficult to say that any one song is solely indie rock. In the end,
    you get the most out of music when you don’t stay within the boundaries of a single
    genre and just explore what sounds you like! </p>

